title: Switzerland Unemployment Rate
description: Unemployment Rate in Switzerland remained unchanged at 1.90 percent in October from 1.90 percent in September of 2022. Unemployment Rate in Switzerland averaged 3.17 percent from 1995 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 5.70 percent in January of 1997 and a record low of 1.50 percent in May of 2001. In Switzerland, the unemployment rate measures the number of people actively looking for a job as a percentage of the labour force. This page provides - Switzerland Unemployment Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: State Secretariat for Economic Affairs
